WEBVTT

00:04.004 --> 00:07.007
DAD, HAVE YOU SEEN
MR. NEEDLES?

00:07.007 --> 00:08.609
I CAN´T FIND HIM
ANYWHERE.

00:08.609 --> 00:10.341
I HAVEN´T SEEN HIM.

00:10.341 --> 00:12.683
I´M WORRIED. HE DIDN´T EAT
ANY OF THE FOOD IN HIS BOWL.

00:12.683 --> 00:15.146
POUR A LITTLE BACON FAT
IN HIS FOOD.

00:15.146 --> 00:17.218
MY MOM USED TO DO THAT
WITH MY DOG.

00:17.218 --> 00:19.590
HE´D LICK THE BOWL CLEAN.

00:19.590 --> 00:24.325
MAYBE THAT´S WHY HE DIED
WHEN HE WAS 3.

00:24.325 --> 00:27.158
I JUST FOUND MR. NEEDLES
HIDING UNDER THE COUCH.

00:27.158 --> 00:29.160
HE DOESN´T LOOK SO GOOD.

00:29.160 --> 00:31.132
YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:31.132 --> 00:33.033
I THINK I SHOULD
CALL THE VET.

00:33.033 --> 00:35.366
NO, NOT DR. LISPY.
EVERY TIME WE GO TO THAT GUY,

00:35.366 --> 00:37.538
HE ALWAYS FINDS SOMETHING
WRONG WITH MR. NEEDLES

00:37.538 --> 00:39.340
JUST SO HE CAN CHARGE US
A FORTUNE.

00:39.340 --> 00:42.113
GEORGE, HE´S NOT
MAKING THINGS UP.

00:42.113 --> 00:44.175
THAT DOG HAS BEEN
THROUGH A LOT

00:44.175 --> 00:46.377
WITH THE DIABETES,
THE CATARACTS,

00:46.377 --> 00:48.119
THE HEART MURMUR.

00:48.119 --> 00:51.182
HE DIDN´T HAVE A HEART MURMUR.
IT JUST SKIPPED A BEAT

00:51.182 --> 00:54.685
WHEN HE SAW THAT GIANT
THERMOMETER HEADING SOUTH.

00:54.685 --> 00:56.357
FINE. I WON´T CALL
DR. LISPY.

00:56.357 --> 00:58.689
BUT I AM TAKING THE PHONE
INTO THE OTHER ROOM

00:58.689 --> 01:00.691
FOR A COUPLE MINUTES.
I MAY TAKE THE DOG OUT

01:00.691 --> 01:02.633
FOR A LITTLE WHILE LATER,

01:02.633 --> 01:04.695
AND THERE MAY BE A BILL
FROM THE VET.

01:04.695 --> 01:07.468
BUT YOU WON, GEORGE.
YOU WON AGAIN.

01:07.468 --> 01:10.301
DARN YOUR STRENGTH.

01:10.301 --> 01:13.304
YOU KNOW, IF YOU DON´T WANT
TO SPEND ANY MONEY,

01:13.304 --> 01:15.346
YOU CAN DO WHAT MY UNCLE DID
WHEN HE WAS SICK.

01:15.346 --> 01:19.510
ERNIE, I´M NOT GOING TO KILL
A CHICKEN TO SAVE A DOG.

01:19.510 --> 01:21.352
NO, MY OTHER UNCLE.

01:21.352 --> 01:25.386
SEE, BASICALLY, HE HAD A CYST
THE SIZE OF A GRAPEFRUIT.

01:25.386 --> 01:27.618
SO HE PRAYED FOR A MIRACLE.

01:27.618 --> 01:29.420
HE PROMISED GOD
THAT IF IT WENT AWAY,

01:29.420 --> 01:32.563
HE´D GO TO MEXICO
AND CRAWL ON HIS KNEES

01:32.563 --> 01:34.395
UP THE COBBLESTONE PATH
THAT LEADS

01:34.395 --> 01:37.128
TO THE CHURCH OF THE VIRGIN
OF GUADALUPE.

01:37.128 --> 01:39.670
A MONTH LATER,
THAT CYST WAS GONE.

01:39.670 --> 01:42.403
iVáMANOS, CYST!
[ Speaks Spanish ]

01:42.403 --> 01:44.505
HE CAN SEE MR. NEEDLES
IN HALF AN HOUR.

01:44.505 --> 01:47.338
YOU KNOW, WHEN I WAS A KID,
WE DIDN´T GO TO THE VET.

01:47.338 --> 01:49.640
MY MOM JUST WAITED
TILL IT GOT DARK

01:49.640 --> 01:52.413
AND THEN WE TOOK THAT DOG
FOR A RIDE.

01:52.413 --> 01:54.215
THAT IS SO MEAN.

01:54.215 --> 01:57.418
NO, IT WASN´T. WE ALWAYS DROPPED
HIM OFF IN A GOOD NEIGHBORHOOD.

01:57.418 --> 01:59.620
THEY HAD STREET LIGHTS...

01:59.620 --> 02:01.892
ALL THE CARS WERE PAINTED
ONE COLOR...

02:01.892 --> 02:05.396
NOBODY WAS SELLING CORN.

02:05.396 --> 02:09.460
WHEN MY MOM OPENED THE DOOR,
I SHOULD´VE JUMPED OUT.

02:12.833 --> 02:16.237
ANGIE. STOP CRADLING THAT DOG
LIKE HE´S A CHILD.

02:16.237 --> 02:18.309
IF THE DOCTOR SEES THAT,
HE´S GOING TO GET US

02:18.309 --> 02:20.611
FOR AS MUCH MONEY
AS HE CAN.

02:20.611 --> 02:24.275
BUT I DO CONSIDER MR. NEEDLES
ONE OF OUR CHILDREN.

02:24.275 --> 02:27.648
THAT´S JUST ´CAUSE CARMEN
SET THE BAR SO LOW.

02:27.648 --> 02:30.181
I´M SORRY I KEPT
YOU FOLKS WAITING.

02:30.181 --> 02:33.324
AND, FRANKLY, I WISH
I HAD BETTER NEWS.

02:33.324 --> 02:36.757
HOW MUCH?

02:36.757 --> 02:39.530
STOP IT. WE´RE NOT
SHOPPING FOR A CAR.

02:39.530 --> 02:41.932
YEAH, BUT HE MIGHT BE.

02:41.932 --> 02:45.696
MR. NEEDLES HAS A TUMOR
IN HIS STOMACH.

02:45.696 --> 02:48.539
OH, MY BABY.

02:48.539 --> 02:50.471
IT´S ALREADY SHOWN SIGNS
OF SPREADING,

02:50.471 --> 02:53.644
BUT HE HAS A SLIM CHANCE
IF WE OPERATE QUICKLY.

02:53.644 --> 02:57.378
HOW MUCH?

02:57.378 --> 02:59.550
WELL, THAT DEPENDS
ON A LOT OF THINGS.

02:59.550 --> 03:03.414
BUT YOU CAN´T PUT A PRICE
ON A FAMILY MEMBER.

03:03.414 --> 03:04.715
OH, YEAH?

03:04.715 --> 03:07.788
MY SON -- 5 GRAND.

03:07.788 --> 03:09.360
MY DAUGHTER --

03:09.360 --> 03:10.961
$2,200.

03:10.961 --> 03:14.825
MY MOM -- FREE,
IF YOU TOW HER AWAY.

03:16.897 --> 03:19.330
DR. LISPY, HOW MUCH WILL
THE OPERATION COST?

03:19.330 --> 03:21.232
AROUND $3,000.

03:21.232 --> 03:24.275
$3,000! THAT LOCO!
$3,000!

03:24.275 --> 03:28.208
ARE THERE ANY OTHER
OPTIONS?

03:28.208 --> 03:30.741
WELL, IF YOU DECIDE
AGAINST THE OPERATION,

03:30.741 --> 03:32.743
THE HUMANE THING TO DO

03:32.743 --> 03:36.787
WOULD BE
TO PUT MR. NEEDLES TO SLEEP.

03:36.787 --> 03:38.749
I´M SORRY, BABY.

03:38.749 --> 03:41.452
WHY DON´T YOU TAKE A NIGHT
TO THINK ABOUT IT?

03:41.452 --> 03:43.954
YOU CAN LEAVE HIM HERE,
AND WE´LL KEEP AN EYE ON HIM.

03:43.954 --> 03:45.956
HOW MUCH DOES
THAT COST?

03:45.956 --> 03:48.499
WELL, THAT DEPENDS
ON A LOT OF VARIABLES.

03:48.499 --> 03:50.661
IF YOU WANT HIM TO HAVE HIS
OWN ROOM, A PRIVATE NURSE...

03:50.661 --> 03:52.663
HOW MUCH?
$150.

03:52.663 --> 03:54.435
NO WAY! FOR 150 BUCKS,

03:54.435 --> 03:56.807
I CAN GET HIM A HOTEL ROOM
AND A HOT POODLE

03:56.807 --> 03:58.809
AND SEND HIM OFF
IN STYLE!

03:58.809 --> 04:01.412
[ Speaks Spanish ]...
ALL NIGHT LONG!

04:03.574 --> 04:06.277
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING TONIGHT?

04:20.991 --> 04:22.963
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS ♫

04:22.963 --> 04:24.695
♫ KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

04:26.837 --> 04:30.301
♫ THE LOW RIDER ♫

04:30.301 --> 04:31.802
♫ IS A LITTLE HIGHER ♫

04:54.565 --> 04:56.727
George: ANGIE, I DON´T
WANT THE DOG TO DIE.

04:56.727 --> 04:58.529
BUT 3 GRAND?

04:58.529 --> 05:01.332
WHAT IF ONE OF THE KIDS
GETS SICK OR HURT?

05:01.332 --> 05:03.434
YOU KNOW, CARMEN´S GOING
TO BE DRIVING NEXT YEAR.

05:03.434 --> 05:05.606
PRETTY SOON, WE´LL BE PAYING
FOR SMASHED FENDERS

05:05.606 --> 05:09.980
AND STREET SIGNS,
OLD PEOPLE, COFFEE SHOPS.

05:11.782 --> 05:15.315
"WAS I GOING THE WRONG WAY?

05:15.315 --> 05:18.349
I THOUGHT EVERYONE WAS WAVING
AT ME BECAUSE I LOOK SO GOOD."

05:18.349 --> 05:21.352
[ IMITATES TRUCK HORN ]

05:21.352 --> 05:24.555
WHEN WE TOOK THAT DOG IN,
WE MADE A COMMITMENT

05:24.555 --> 05:26.627
TO TAKE CARE OF HIM,
NO MATTER WHAT.

05:26.627 --> 05:30.401
AND WE HAVE. I MEAN, WE NURSED
THAT DOG THROUGH DIABETES

05:30.401 --> 05:32.032
AND MANGE...

05:32.032 --> 05:35.436
ERUPTING TAIL ACNE...

05:35.436 --> 05:38.338
IF I HAD ALL THAT STUFF,
ANGIE, I´D BE BEGGING YOU

05:38.338 --> 05:41.071
TO BURY ME IN THE BACKYARD.

05:41.071 --> 05:43.914
IF I HAD TO DIG A HOLE
BIG ENOUGH FOR YOUR HEAD,

05:43.914 --> 05:47.448
I´D RATHER PUT IN A POOL.

05:51.422 --> 05:54.054
LOOK, ANGIE,
YOU HEARD THE VET.

05:54.054 --> 05:56.387
EVEN WITH THE OPERATION,
THERE´S A GOOD CHANCE

05:56.387 --> 05:58.629
THAT THE DISEASE
HAS ALREADY SPREAD.

05:58.629 --> 06:01.892
I KNOW YOU´RE UPSET, BUT I DON´T
THINK WE HAVE A CHOICE HERE.

06:04.735 --> 06:06.837
YOU WANT ME TO TELL MAX?

06:06.837 --> 06:08.138
NO, I´LL DO IT.

06:08.138 --> 06:10.571
WHAT ARE YOU DOING TO SAY?

06:10.571 --> 06:12.873
I DON´T KNOW. I GUESS
I COULD USE THE SPEECH

06:12.873 --> 06:14.945
I PREPARED
FOR MY MOM´S DEATH.

06:14.945 --> 06:16.977
I JUST WON´T START IT
WITH,

06:16.977 --> 06:22.052
"THE REASON I´M DRINKING
CHAMPAGNE IS BECAUSE..."

06:30.020 --> 06:32.663
HEY, BUDDY,
WHERE´S MR. NEEDLES?

06:32.663 --> 06:36.727
HE WAS GASSY, SO I PUT HIM
IN CARMEN´S ROOM.

06:36.727 --> 06:40.571
LOOK, WE GOTTA TALK.

06:42.002 --> 06:45.976
MR. NEEDLES HAS A TUMOR
IN HIS STOMACH.

06:45.976 --> 06:49.780
I´M SORRY, SON, BUT IT DOESN´T
LOOK LIKE HE´S GOING TO MAKE IT.

06:49.780 --> 06:52.112
BUT...HE´S BEEN SICK
BEFORE.

06:52.112 --> 06:55.946
HE ALWAYS GETS BETTER.

06:55.946 --> 06:58.148
NOT THIS TIME, MAX.

06:58.148 --> 07:01.021
MR. NEEDLES
IS IN A LOT OF PAIN.

07:01.021 --> 07:04.495
YOU DON´T WANT HIM
TO GO THROUGH THAT, DO YOU?

07:04.495 --> 07:07.097
NO.

07:07.097 --> 07:09.600
AND NEITHER DO WE, SO...

07:09.600 --> 07:13.033
TOMORROW, WE´RE GOING
TO TAKE HIM TO THE VET AND...

07:13.033 --> 07:14.505
END HIS SUFFERING.

07:14.505 --> 07:17.007
SO WE STILL GOT
ONE MORE NIGHT.

07:17.007 --> 07:19.169
HE MIGHT GET BETTER.

07:19.169 --> 07:21.872
I DON´T THINK
THAT´S GOING TO HAPPEN, SON.

07:21.872 --> 07:23.143
IT COULD.

07:25.976 --> 07:30.450
GOD, IF YOU SAVE MR. NEEDLES,
I´LL...

07:30.450 --> 07:34.224
I´LL BE NICE TO CARMEN
FOR A WHOLE MONTH.

07:35.856 --> 07:37.988
AREN´T YOU GOING TO PRAY?

07:37.988 --> 07:41.461
OKAY. SURE.

07:43.894 --> 07:45.996
I HOPE MR. NEEDLES
GETS BETTER,

07:45.996 --> 07:48.769
BUT I´M NOT EXPECTING
ANYTHING.

07:48.769 --> 07:50.701
DAD!

07:50.701 --> 07:52.943
I JUST DON´T WANT YOU
TO GET YOUR HOPES UP.

07:52.943 --> 07:55.045
BUT YOU HEARD ERNIE.

07:55.045 --> 07:57.508
PRAYING WORKED FOR HIS UNCLE.

07:59.510 --> 08:03.654
OKAY.

08:03.654 --> 08:06.016
[ GROANS ]

08:09.520 --> 08:12.793
AGAIN, I´M NOT
EXPECTING ANYTHING.

08:16.827 --> 08:19.129
BUT, GOD,

08:19.129 --> 08:22.703
IF YOU MAKE MR. NEEDLES
GET BETTER,

08:22.703 --> 08:25.205
I WILL CRAWL UP
THE COBBLESTONE PATH

08:25.205 --> 08:28.078
TO THAT CHURCH IN MEXICO.

08:29.640 --> 08:31.682
THANKS, DAD.

08:31.682 --> 08:33.083
OKAY.

08:33.083 --> 08:34.514
JUST REMEMBER,

08:34.514 --> 08:36.516
IF THE PRAYERS
DON´T WORK,

08:36.516 --> 08:38.849
MR. NEEDLES WILL GO
STRAIGHT TO HEAVEN,

08:38.849 --> 08:42.823
AND HE´LL BE ABLE TO RUN AGAIN
AND LIFT HIS LEG AND PEE...

08:42.823 --> 08:45.195
AND HE´LL BE THAT FEISTY
LITTLE GUY HE WAS

08:45.195 --> 08:47.698
BEFORE HE GOT NEUTERED.

08:47.698 --> 08:48.759
REALLY?

08:48.759 --> 08:50.300
YEP.

08:50.300 --> 08:52.633
EVERY TIME A BELL RINGS,
SON,

08:52.633 --> 08:55.566
ANOTHER DOG GETS BACK
HIS HUEVOS.

09:03.013 --> 09:08.548
[ BARKING ]

09:08.548 --> 09:10.981
I´M TELLING YOU,
MR. NEEDLES IS BETTER.

09:10.981 --> 09:12.883
HE´S BEEN LIKE THIS
ALL DAY.

09:12.883 --> 09:15.255
HE DID FINISH
ALL HIS FOOD THIS MORNING.

09:15.255 --> 09:17.958
LOOK, YOU TWO
ARE BREAKING MY HEART.

09:17.958 --> 09:21.191
THIS IS A VERY,
VERY SICK DOG.

09:23.994 --> 09:26.336
DOES THAT LOOK SICK
TO YOU?

09:28.599 --> 09:32.302
HE´S SO SAD, ANGIE,
HE´S KISSING HIS ASS GOODBYE.

09:40.180 --> 09:43.053
DOGS KNOW.

09:43.053 --> 09:45.355
HE KNOWS.

09:47.217 --> 09:51.091
OKAY, UH, WE TOOK
MORE X-RAYS

09:51.091 --> 09:53.223
LIKE MRS. LOPEZ
REQUESTED.

09:53.223 --> 09:55.896
LISTEN, WE CAN´T FIND
THE TUMOR.

09:55.896 --> 09:58.629
IT´S JUST...

09:58.629 --> 09:59.830
DISAPPEARED.

09:59.830 --> 10:02.032
I TOLD YOU!

10:02.032 --> 10:04.174
WHOA, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT A MINUTE,

10:04.174 --> 10:05.676
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
"DISAPPEARED"?

10:05.676 --> 10:08.078
TAKE A LOOK FOR YOURSELF
AT THE X-RAYS.

10:08.078 --> 10:10.781
YESTERDAY, TUMOR.
TODAY...

10:10.781 --> 10:12.012
NO TUMOR.

10:12.012 --> 10:14.184
AND YOU CAN TELL
IT´S THE SAME DOG

10:14.184 --> 10:16.847
BECAUSE HE SWALLOWED
THIS HEART-SHAPED EARRING.

10:16.847 --> 10:20.290
OH, I´VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR THAT.

10:20.290 --> 10:23.754
AND I THINK YOU´LL BE
FINDING IT VERY SOON.

10:28.198 --> 10:32.362
DOCTOR, HOW DOES A TUMOR
JUST DISAPPEAR?

10:32.362 --> 10:34.965
IF I HAD TO GUESS,

10:34.965 --> 10:37.237
I´D SAY IT´S A MIRACLE.

10:39.409 --> 10:43.243
GOD HEARD US.
THE PRAYERS WORKED.

10:43.243 --> 10:45.876
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

10:45.876 --> 10:48.218
I PROMISED GOD
I´D BE NICE TO CARMEN

10:48.218 --> 10:50.280
IF HE SAVED MR. NEEDLES.

10:50.280 --> 10:52.953
DAD MADE A PROMISE, TOO.

11:00.330 --> 11:02.392
WHAT DID YOU PROMISE?

11:02.392 --> 11:06.666
HA. NOT--
NOTHING, REALLY.

11:08.368 --> 11:14.074
HE HAS TO CRAWL ON HIS KNEES
TO SOME CHURCH IN MEXICO.

11:14.074 --> 11:16.246
REALLY?

11:19.249 --> 11:21.712
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
UP THERE?

11:23.854 --> 11:26.286
YOU KNOW, IF YOU´RE LISTENING
TO ME NOW,

11:26.286 --> 11:29.389
I WANT TWO MORE WISHES.

11:29.389 --> 11:31.461
IT DOESN´T WORK
THAT WAY.

11:31.461 --> 11:34.795
WHAT DO YOU KNOW?
YOU´VE NEVER SAVED A DOG.

11:39.930 --> 11:41.932
HOW IS MR. NEEDLES?

11:41.932 --> 11:43.874
HE´S DOING GREAT.

11:43.874 --> 11:47.137
DAD, WHEN ARE YOU GOING
TO MEXICO

11:47.137 --> 11:50.040
AND GO CRAWL
ON YOUR KNEES?

11:50.040 --> 11:52.142
YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:52.142 --> 11:55.085
GOD CAME TO ME LAST NIGHT
IN A VISION.

11:58.248 --> 12:01.822
I DON´T HAVE TO GO ANYMORE.

12:01.822 --> 12:03.053
YEAH?

12:03.053 --> 12:05.295
WHAT´D HE SAY?

12:05.295 --> 12:09.860
IT WAS ALL A BIG MIX-UP.

12:09.860 --> 12:12.462
IT TURNS OUT HE WAS TRYING
TO SAVE SOME DOG IN CHINA --

12:12.462 --> 12:15.135
MR. NOODLES.

12:18.068 --> 12:20.240
THAT IS THE LAMEST EXCUSE
I´VE EVER HEARD.

12:20.240 --> 12:22.843
WAIT TILL TOMORROW.

12:26.076 --> 12:28.078
YOU KNOW YOU CAN´T
PUT THIS OFF FOREVER.

12:28.078 --> 12:30.250
MAX IS GOING TO BUG YOU
ABOUT THIS EVERY DAY

12:30.250 --> 12:32.122
FOR THE REST
OF YOUR LIFE.

12:32.122 --> 12:34.524
ANGIE, I CAN´T GO TO MEXICO
AND CRAWL ON MY KNEES.

12:34.524 --> 12:36.787
ERNIE TOLD ME THE PATH
TO THAT CHURCH

12:36.787 --> 12:39.089
IS A MILE OF ROUGH
COBBLESTONES.

12:39.089 --> 12:41.191
WELL, YOU SHOULD´VE THOUGHT
ABOUT THAT

12:41.191 --> 12:43.964
BEFORE YOU MADE A PROMISE
TO GOD IN FRONT OF YOUR SON.

12:43.964 --> 12:46.837
I THOUGHT THE DOG
WAS ON HIS WAY OUT!

12:50.140 --> 12:53.373
AND NOW I´M BEING PUNISHED
FOR TRYING TO COMFORT MY BOY?

12:53.373 --> 12:56.246
WHAT KIND OF SICK GAME
IS THIS?

12:56.246 --> 12:58.508
IT´S NOT A GAME.

12:58.508 --> 13:01.251
WHAT HAPPENED WITH THAT DOG
IS A MIRACLE.

13:01.251 --> 13:03.483
COME ON, DON´T TELL ME
YOU BELIEVE THAT.

13:03.483 --> 13:05.886
Angie: THEN YOU EXPLAIN IT.

13:05.886 --> 13:08.989
I CAN´T. I ALSO CAN´T EXPLAIN
WHY MARTIN SHEEN IS A LATINO,

13:08.989 --> 13:11.491
BUT THAT DOESN´T
MAKE SENSE, EITHER.

13:13.263 --> 13:16.496
FINE. BLOW OFF GOD,
BUT DON´T BLAME ME

13:16.496 --> 13:18.798
WHEN YOUR HANDS TURN
TO SERPENTS

13:18.798 --> 13:20.200
AND START BITING
YOUR FACE.

13:20.200 --> 13:23.503
SSS -- OW! SSS -- OW!
SSS -- OW! SSS -- OW!

13:23.503 --> 13:25.335
LOOK, ANGIE, PLEASE,

13:25.335 --> 13:28.208
IF GOD PUNISHED EVERYONE WHO
BROKE HIS PROMISE TO HIM

13:28.208 --> 13:31.141
THE WORLD WOULD BE FILLED
WITH WAR AND FAMINE.

13:31.141 --> 13:34.114
IT IS.

13:36.186 --> 13:38.418
DAD´S RIGHT.

13:38.418 --> 13:40.350
PEOPLE MAKE PROMISES
ALL THE TIME,

13:40.350 --> 13:42.192
AND THEY NEVER
FOLLOW THROUGH.

13:42.192 --> 13:44.855
JASON PROMISED TO TAKE ME
TO A MOVIE TONIGHT,

13:44.855 --> 13:47.097
THEN JUST BLEW ME OFF
AT BASKETBALL PRACTICE.

13:47.097 --> 13:49.329
BUT I COULDN´T SAY ANYTHING,
´CAUSE IF I´M MAD AT HIM,

13:49.329 --> 13:51.501
HE MIGHT BREAK UP WITH ME,
AND ALL I WANT TO DO

13:51.501 --> 13:53.833
IS KEEP BEING
JASON McNAMARA´S GIRLFRIEND!

13:58.869 --> 14:00.941
I MIGHT GO TO MEXICO

14:00.941 --> 14:04.274
JUST TO GET THE HELL
OUT OF THE HOUSE.

14:04.274 --> 14:06.516
[ MUTTERS IN SPANISH ]

14:08.278 --> 14:10.580
IF YOU DON´T FOLLOW THROUGH
WITH THIS

14:10.580 --> 14:12.622
AND ANYTHING HAPPENS
TO MR. NEEDLES,

14:12.622 --> 14:14.955
MAX WILL NEVER FORGIVE YOU.

14:14.955 --> 14:18.588
I CAN NEVER DO NOTHING
IN THIS HOUSE.

14:19.960 --> 14:23.263
THEY´RE ALL CRAZY
IN THERE.

14:23.263 --> 14:26.166
WHY DO YOU THINK
I´M OUT HERE?

14:30.540 --> 14:32.602
LET´S SEE --

14:32.602 --> 14:36.276
SMOKE OR TALK TO ANGIE?

14:36.276 --> 14:39.349
WELL, THEY BOTH
SHORTEN MY LIFE.

14:39.349 --> 14:40.911
BUT, YOU KNOW,

14:40.911 --> 14:43.883
THE TAX ON THESE
HELPS PAY FOR PUBLIC SCHOOLS.

14:45.415 --> 14:49.659
THIS ONE´S FOR THE KIDS.

14:51.291 --> 14:54.094
I´M NOT GOING TO GO
TO MEXICO AND CRAWL ON MY KNEES.

14:54.094 --> 14:57.067
OH, GEORGE, IT DOESN´T MATTER
IF YOU ACTUALLY GO

14:57.067 --> 14:59.899
AS LONG
AS MAX THINKS YOU WENT.

14:59.899 --> 15:02.302
MA, I´M NOT GOING
TO LIE TO HIM.

15:02.302 --> 15:03.903
WHY NOT?

15:03.903 --> 15:06.306
HE´LL NEVER FIND OUT.

15:06.306 --> 15:09.039
GEORGE, REMEMBER WHEN
YOU WERE LITTLE

15:09.039 --> 15:11.211
AND I TOOK YOU
TO DISNEYLAND?

15:17.587 --> 15:19.589
YEAH.

15:19.589 --> 15:22.422
IT WAS JUST A CARNIVAL

15:22.422 --> 15:26.226
IN A CHURCH PARKING LOT.

15:31.931 --> 15:34.334
BUT THERE WAS
DISNEY CHARACTERS THERE.

15:34.334 --> 15:35.935
NOPE, NOPE.

15:35.935 --> 15:38.638
THOSE DWARVES
YOU WERE HUGGING --

15:38.638 --> 15:41.041
THEY WERE JUST DWARVES.

15:46.076 --> 15:47.978
I CAN´T BELIEVE
YOU DID THAT.

15:47.978 --> 15:50.080
GEORGE, COME ON.

15:50.080 --> 15:52.482
WE WERE BROKE.
I WANTED YOU TO BE HAPPY.

15:52.482 --> 15:54.724
IT WORKED, DIDN´T IT?

15:54.724 --> 15:56.956
I GUESS.

15:56.956 --> 15:58.728
WHAT ABOUT SEA WORLD
WITH THE LOBSTER TANK

15:58.728 --> 16:01.231
AND THAT REALLY GOOD
GARLIC BREAD?

16:05.095 --> 16:08.038
LET´S NOT
GO DOWN THIS ROAD.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.651
HEY, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING?

16:21.651 --> 16:26.186
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE DOWN IN MEXICO.

16:26.186 --> 16:28.718
AS FAR AS MAX KNOWS,
I AM.

16:28.718 --> 16:30.520
WHAT?

16:30.520 --> 16:32.522
OH, NO.

16:32.522 --> 16:36.526
YOU´RE GOING TO FAKE
CRAWLING ON THE COBBLESTONES?

16:36.526 --> 16:38.628
THAT´S SACRILEGE.

16:38.628 --> 16:40.730
COME ON.
THIS IS HARMLESS.

16:40.730 --> 16:42.502
IT´S NOT LIKE
I´M TRICKING HIM

16:42.502 --> 16:45.035
INTO HUGGING
A BUNCH OF WASTED DWARVES.

16:45.035 --> 16:50.080
OKAY, HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN HERE DRINKING?

16:50.080 --> 16:52.742
LOOK, FATHER RICK
JUST WALKED IN.

16:52.742 --> 16:55.545
GEORGE, IT´S A SIGN.

16:55.545 --> 16:58.788
HE´S JUST PICKING UP MONEY FROM
THE DONATION JAR. IT´S A SIGN.

16:58.788 --> 17:02.322
LOOK, GEORGE,
THEN WHY IS HE COMING OVER?

17:02.322 --> 17:04.023
HOW ARE YOU?

17:04.023 --> 17:06.196
I´M GOOD, MAN.
TAKE CARE.

17:08.358 --> 17:10.230
HOW´S IT GOING,
ERNESTO?

17:10.230 --> 17:12.632
GEORGE IS LYING
TO HIS SON AND GOD,

17:12.632 --> 17:15.635
AND YOU´VE BEEN SENT
DOWN HERE TO SAVE HIM.

17:15.635 --> 17:19.109
IS THERE SOMETHING YOU WANT
TO GET OFF YOUR CHEST, GEORGE?

17:21.111 --> 17:22.342
YOU GOT A MINUTE?

17:22.342 --> 17:23.643
SURE.

17:23.643 --> 17:26.446
LOOK, FATHER,
MY KID´S DOG WAS DYING,

17:26.446 --> 17:29.719
SO I PROMISED GOD
THAT IF HE LIVED -- HA HA --

17:29.719 --> 17:32.122
I´D CRAWL UP
THE COBBLESTONE PATH

17:32.122 --> 17:34.624
TO THE CHURCH
OF THE VIRGIN OF GUADALUPE.

17:34.624 --> 17:39.089
I´VE HEARD THOSE COBBLESTONES
ARE LIKE JAGGED KNIVES

17:39.089 --> 17:42.092
CUTTING AWAY
AT YOUR KNEES.

17:42.092 --> 17:44.434
ANYWAY, MAN,
THE DOG GOT BETTER.

17:44.434 --> 17:46.296
NO ONE KNOWS HOW.

17:46.296 --> 17:48.668
SO NOW MY SON
WANTS ME TO GO TO MEXICO,

17:48.668 --> 17:51.201
BUT I ONLY SAID THE PRAYER
TO MAKE HIM FEEL BETTER.

17:51.201 --> 17:54.204
WELL, GEORGE, IN THE BIBLE,
GOD DOESN´T BARGAIN.

17:54.204 --> 17:56.846
YOU DON´T OFFER HIM THINGS
TO GET THINGS IN RETURN.

17:56.846 --> 17:59.078
THANK YOU.

17:59.078 --> 18:01.251
THAT´S PERFECT.
THAT´S WHAT I CAN TELL MAX.

18:01.251 --> 18:03.183
WHY DOES IT TAKE YOU GUYS
AN HOUR

18:03.183 --> 18:06.386
TO SAY THE SAME THING
ON SUNDAYS?

18:09.389 --> 18:11.221
THEN AGAIN,
YOU DID MAKE A PROMISE,

18:11.221 --> 18:13.123
AND IF YOU DON´T
KEEP YOUR WORD,

18:13.123 --> 18:14.594
THAT´S BEARING
FALSE WITNESS,

18:14.594 --> 18:17.227
WHICH WOULD BE
BREAKING A COMMANDMENT.

18:18.798 --> 18:22.702
BUT IT´S NOT, LIKE, ONE
OF THE BIG COMMANDMENTS, RIGHT?

18:22.702 --> 18:24.134
LIKE KILLING OR STEALING.

18:24.134 --> 18:26.136
I MEAN, COME ON,
GOD JUST KIND OF

18:26.136 --> 18:29.209
THREW THAT ONE IN
TO FILL UP THE TABLETS.

18:29.209 --> 18:31.181
I MEAN,
"THE NINE COMMANDMENTS" --

18:31.181 --> 18:33.543
THAT SOUNDS KIND OF LAME.

18:33.543 --> 18:37.116
ULTIMATELY, GEORGE,
YOU HAVE TO ASK YOURSELF

18:37.116 --> 18:39.719
DO YOU WANT TO BE A MAN
WHO KEEPS HIS WORD

18:39.719 --> 18:42.121
OR A LIAR?

18:44.694 --> 18:48.258
OKAY.

18:48.258 --> 18:51.531
LET´S SAY I DON´T
DO THIS COBBLESTONE THING,

18:51.531 --> 18:54.534
BUT I DO SOMETHING
JUST AS GOOD.

18:54.534 --> 18:56.766
LET´S SAY I GIVE
A LITTLE SOMETHING-SOMETHING

18:56.766 --> 19:00.570
TO THE CHURCH.

19:00.570 --> 19:04.414
LET´S SAY -- HUH?
[ Whistles ]

19:04.414 --> 19:08.218
GEORGE, IS THAT A FOUR
OR A SEVEN?

19:08.218 --> 19:11.150
THAT IS A ONE, MY MAN.

19:11.150 --> 19:13.323
HAVE A NICE TIME
IN MEXICO.

19:25.695 --> 19:28.568
OH, MAN,
THIS IS TOUGH.

19:28.568 --> 19:32.342
YOU KNOW, WE COULD WALK
A LITTLE BIT ON OUR FEET,

19:32.342 --> 19:33.743
AND NOBODY WOULD KNOW.

19:33.743 --> 19:35.875
GOD WOULD KNOW.

19:35.875 --> 19:38.848
YOU´RE ONE OF THOSE, HUH?

19:38.848 --> 19:40.850
SO WHY ARE YOU HERE?

19:40.850 --> 19:43.383
THERE WAS A HORRIBLE FLOOD.

19:43.383 --> 19:45.855
MY ENTIRE VILLAGE WAS LOST.

19:45.855 --> 19:48.618
AS I CLUTCHED
TO THE TOP OF A TREE

19:48.618 --> 19:50.590
AND THE WATERS ROSE,

19:50.590 --> 19:53.823
I PROMISED GOD
IF HE SPARED MY LIFE,

19:53.823 --> 19:56.566
I WOULD CRAWL THIS PATH.

19:56.566 --> 19:57.967
AND YOU?

20:01.871 --> 20:04.574
MY KID´S DOG GOT SICK.

20:12.782 --> 20:15.785
HERE, HONEY.

20:15.785 --> 20:17.216
AH.

20:17.216 --> 20:19.349
ANYTHING ELSE
BEFORE I GO?

20:19.349 --> 20:21.851
NO, I´M ALL RIGHT.

20:21.851 --> 20:24.524
ALL RIGHT. I´M GOING TO GO
GET YOUR PAIN MEDICATION.

20:27.927 --> 20:31.561
I´LL BE RIGHT BACK.

20:34.664 --> 20:36.836
OKAY, I GET IT.
YOU´RE WELCOME.

20:36.836 --> 20:37.907
[ FLATULENCE ]

20:37.907 --> 20:40.570
WHAT WAS THAT?

20:40.570 --> 20:41.871
[ FLATULENCE ]

20:41.871 --> 20:43.973
OH, COME ON.
I CAN´T MOVE.

20:43.973 --> 20:45.515
GO TO CARMEN´S ROOM.

20:45.515 --> 20:47.617
NEEDLES,
GO TO CARMEN´S ROOM. GO.

20:47.617 --> 20:50.620
[ FLATULENCE ]

20:50.620 --> 21:00.530
I THINK I KNOW
WHAT KILLED THAT TUMOR.
